        "timestamp": "2017-09-26 09:09:49.000000000",
        "message": "Patch Set 1: Code-Review-1\n\n1.\tThere will be other repositories to account for so we do not see the implementation to be as suggested in terms of a button in the upload file box. As said I’m talking to UX expert about it.\n2.\tAs for the code provided:\na.\tCommented code should not be there at all. I’ve seen it all around the files.\nb.\tUpload file box is used in other screens as well so it cannot be modified, in a way that affects other screens (also as stated, ux will not be like that most likely)\nc.\tSuggest that the name VNFCreationReducer is not correct enough – perhaps VNFImportReducer  ?\nd.\tAlso wondering if vnfmarketplace should be placed under onboarding/softwareProduct/vnfMarketPlace and not under onboarding/vnfMarketPlace. Any specific reason you chose that?\ne.\tThere is no i18n on the VNFCreationView for the header names\nf.\tWhat are the date related styles ? I do not see any date in the files… ?\ng.\t Do not keep debugging console.logs when submitting your code (example: SoftwareProductLandingPage.js)\nh.\tIn the store, please name the section similarly to other naming convention – i.e. do not use the word reducer, rather something like: VNFMarketPlaceImport\ni.\tIn the VNFCreation.js , just deconstruct the prop instead\nj.\tWe are not using jquery for rest calls. Currently use RestAPIUtil. There is no jquery here at all. RESTAPIUtil is in the process of being replaced so it also does not use jquery\nk.\tURL cannot be hard coded into the code and also current url is local???\nl.\tIf error occurs in the get, there should be an error modal.\nm.\tYou are using a Form, but you don’t have any input fields and you do not require data validation, so it seems like an overkill. Maybe just use the local state? (By the way you are also using the Form incorrectly, each form has a name, and other issues we can discuss if you do need it)",
        "patchset_number": 1
      },
